comments.body:
IF(OR(G4=0, NOT(ISBLANK(J4))),J4,IF(AND(J4="",G4>0,G4=G3+1),K3,INDEX(K$2:K3,MATCH(2,1/(G$2:G3=G4-1)))))

If level is 0 (i.e., collection) or restriction note is present, grab what's in the original restriction note field.
Else, if restriction note is blank and level is greater than 0 and level is one greater than preceding, grab preceding computed restriction note,
else find parent and grab its computed restriction note.

Plan:

Move from polling the manifest for authorization to getting all the info we need from the graphql endpoint
Update the getResourcesByOrangelightIds query to return an object like

```
{ ...
  embed: {
    html: 
    status:
  }
}
```

Where html is either an iframe or a link and status could be "unauthenticated", "unauthorized", or "authorized".

If unauthenticated or unauthorized then html is nil unless the resource is public.
